    <h1>M2SQL Interactive SQL Shell</h1>
    <h2>Operator Reference & Terminal REPL Guide</h2>
    
    <p>The <code>M2SQL Shell</code> provides a high-efficiency Command-Line Interface (REPL) enabling administrators and developers to execute real-time relational expressions directly inside the native environment console, utilizing complete embedded transaction isolation and rollbacks.</p>

    <h2>How to Launch the Shell</h2>
    <p>To initialize the interactive shell environment, load your standard environment workspace console and trigger the main routine namespace entry point:</p>
    
    <div class="terminal-block">
        M> DO ^MSQ<br>
        <span style="color:#fff;">M2sql > </span>
    </div>

    <h2>Core Features & Supported Commands</h2>
    
    <h3>1. Data Selection (<code>SELECT</code>)</h3>
    <p>Queries database records using the newly engineered dual-loop chunking pipeline. Capable of displaying over 100,000 records dynamically without console rendering choke or memory allocation errors.</p>
    <div class="terminal-block">
        M2sql > select id, name, price from products limit 3<br>
        <span style="color:#fff;">Chunks returned: 1 | Total records: 3<br>
        Row 1: 100|product10|1375.52<br>
        Row 2: 200|product2|857.64<br>
        Row 3: 300|product3|2688.13</span>
    </div>

    <h3>2. Fault-Tolerant DML Operations (<code>INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE</code>)</h3>
    <p>All data modification changes are explicitly wrapped inside automated <strong>At-C Transaction Lifecycles</strong> (<code>BEGIN TRANSACTION</code> and <code>COMMIT</code>). If a statement triggers an internal syntax flaw or database execution fail, an automated <code>ROLLBACK</code> is issued instantly, completely eliminating database locks.</p>
    <div class="terminal-block">
        M2sql > update products set price=price*0.88<br>
        <span style="color:#fff;">Execution reply (Rows affected): 329000</span><br><br>
        M2sql > insert into users(id,name) values(400,'Rafi Farchi')<br>
        <span style="color:#fff;">Execution reply (Rows affected): 1</span>
    </div>

    <h2><span style="color:#cf6679;">⚠️</span> Operational Safeguards & Quirks</h2>

    <div class="danger-box">
        <strong>1. Single Quotes Rule for String Values:</strong><br>
        To prevent parsing degradation and nested structure breaks within the communication gateway, string conditions inside your SQL query must be declared with <strong>single quotes ('...')</strong>. Do not use double quotes.<br><br>
        ❌ <code>insert into a(b) values("q")</code> &mdash; <em>Will fail with Internal Execution Error.</em><br>
        ✔️ <code>insert into a(b) values('q')</code> &mdash; <em>Executes perfectly.</em>
    </div>

    <div class="danger-box">
        <strong>2. Strict Command Isolation:</strong><br>
        The shell routing table intercepts jobs by analyzing the first token keyword of the entered terminal sequence. Ensure keywords like <code>SELECT</code>, <code>INSERT</code>, <code>UPDATE</code>, or <code>DELETE</code> are typed clearly at the start of the line.
    </div>

    <h2>Graceful Disconnection</h2>
    <p>To exit the interactive interface safely and return back to the native prompt, issue any of the following parameters:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><code>exit</code></li>
        <li><code>q</code></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="terminal-block">
        M2sql > exit<br>
        M>
    </div>

